data.text:
Goodison Park has has been alive for well over a century and during that time she’s created a mountain of memories.

The Old Lady has seen it all, from dirge draws to brilliant victories. These days as we mix with cold-blooded billionaire run teams with Hollywood smiles, we couldn’t be further from our name the Merseyside Milliaires; but I’m proud of our tousled hair, our gappy grin, and of our Goodison...

50. Everton 4-2 Bolton Wanderers. September 2, 1892
